Nigeria to Keep Troops in Northern City of Maiduguri, Trust Newspaper Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-07-14T08:32:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/nigeria-to-keep-troops-in-northern-city-of-maiduguri-trust-says.html
Nigeria will keep troops deployed to
the northern city of Maiduguri, where the Boko Haram Islamic
sect has claimed a series of attacks,  Daily Trust  said, citing
Andrew Azazi, a retired army general and National Security
Adviser.  The West African nation is working out a new security
structure to protect national infrastructure, including banks,
the Abuja-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 